	<text>
		<body>
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001088_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'--> 
<!--Hand 01 16249. top left--><!--Hand 02 91798 top right--><!-- Hand 03 70 top left-->
<lb/><p rend="right">London 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><choice><abbr>Sept<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>September</expan></choice> 1857</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>Captain Toynbee</persName></p>
<lb/><p>Having been 
<lb/>absent at Dublin 
<lb/>attending a <term>meeting 
<lb/>of the British 
<w>Associ-<lb break="no"/>ation</w></term> there, I did 
<lb/>not see your notes 
<lb/><choice><sic>untill</sic><corr>until</corr></choice> yesterday 
<lb/>evening, I spoke 
<lb/>at a large meeting 
<lb/>on Monday evening 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001088_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>and your notes &amp; 
<lb/>the observations 
<lb/>having in the mean
<lb/>time gone to 
<lb/><placeName>Hadley Green</placeName> I could 
<lb/>not attend to your 
<lb/>invitation to meet 
<lb/>you in London</p>
<lb/><p>I hope this may 
<lb/>catch you and 
<lb/>that you may 
<lb/>know that I am 
<lb/>truly thankful for 
<lb/>all you have done 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001088_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>I have just written 
<lb/><persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Shaw</persName> telling 
<lb/>him that I propose 
<lb/>following your 
<lb/>plan to give the 
<lb/>table of <choice><abbr>Lats</abbr><expan>latitudes</expan></choice> &amp; <choice><abbr>Long.</abbr><expan>longitudes</expan></choice>
<lb/>at the end of the 
<lb/>book and refer 
<lb/>to the more full 
<lb/>details with your 
<lb/>remarks to be 
<lb/>published in the 
<lb/><choice><abbr>R. G.</abbr><expan>Royal Geographical</expan></choice> Journal. <del type="strikethrough" resp="#CO"><!--triple strikethrough-->The</del>
<lb/><persName>Murray</persName> has no 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001088_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'--> 
<lb/><!--Hand 02 91798 top right-->objection to print 
<lb/>150 copies to be 
<lb/>given to any one 
<lb/>who wishes them 
<lb/>apart from the 
<lb/>book but thinks 
<lb/>that 12000 of these 
<lb/>would not be 
<lb/>valued except by 
<lb/>a very few &amp; the 
<lb/>expense is very 
<lb/>great. The <choice><abbr>R. G.</abbr><expan>Royal Geographical</expan></choice>
<lb/>Journal seems the 
<lb/>better vehicle <!--rest of letter missing???--></p><!--Hand 04 Sotheby. 12.12.22.-->
			
